FBIS4-35010 "drlat124_b_94001" FBIS-LAT-94-124 Daily Report 27 Jun 1994 Haiti Bank Governor Denies $500,000 Cedras Withdrawal Bank Governor Denies $500,000 Cedras Withdrawal FL2706211394 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1030 GMT 27 Jun 94 FL2706211394 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio French BFN [Text] Bonivert Claude, governor of the Central Bank of Haiti, denied the allegation that General Raoul Cedras withdrew $500,000. THE WASHINGTON POST had asserted that the head of the Haitian Army, Gen. Cedras, had withdrawn $500,000 from whatever strong currency remains in the Haitian central bank. Quoting government officials and members of Haitian banking circles, the newspaper explained that the reasons for this withdrawal were not clear. Claude exclaims: This is impossible! The general does not have an account at the Central Bank. Claude further pointed out that the bank is concerned with the currency problem affecting the Haitian financial system, and looks for a quick solution to this problem.
